{
  "bio": [
    "Monica Crippa is the daughter of Giuseppe Crippa (d. 2025), the late founder of Technoprobe, an Italian manufacturer of probe cards, small devices that test the functionality of microchips.",
    "Her father founded Technoprobe in 1989 in his garage and attic alongside his son Cristiano, while still working at semiconductor firm ST.",
    "Technoprobe went public on Euronext Milan in 2022; Monica owns a 12% stake.",
    "Monica served on Technoprobe's board until stepping down for personal reasons in 2022."
